{
  "stem": "17761.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 121.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The leading religious figures in that village, in that shul, were my grandfather, who finished the Talmud Bavli a certain something times, learned up to the end of his years-- maybe we'll come to that-- and my father, who finished during his lifetime 20 and something times the Talmud Bavli.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they were the leading figures.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were not-- they weren't rabbis.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They didn't even want to be a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we moved to Vatra-Dornei, that was a totally different setting.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, it was a little town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were streets.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were paved streets.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a huge park, a beautiful park.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were two rivers in that place.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The rivers were the Dorna and the Bistrita.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were the two rivers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They joined next to this city each other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Dorna went into the Bistrita.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There were mountains.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Winter time, there were ski, sliding-- ice sliding and-- how do you call-- sleighs on the snow.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And summertime, people came from all over the world, like to Switzerland, like to St.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Moritz.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we knew there a lot of people of-- some of them prominent people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "During summer, we could have a few tens of rabbis or rabbis, big rabbis, famous people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] used to come every year to our-- to our city.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH], I could mention a lot of them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We had the chief rabbi of Romania, Rabbi Niemirower, who came to our place in certain years.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Came people from Israel like Rabbi Fischman, Rabbi Neufeld.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And [NON-ENGLISH] came to that place on the summer, because there were about 10,000 people who used to come to this place during the summer.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So I heard there the famous Cantor of Tschernowitz, Moshe [?",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
